    "created_at": "2017-04-17T04:53:03Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-04-17T04:53:03Z",
    "body": "As far as I can tell this is part of the spec for the TouchBar, if any item would exceed the available space it is either cropped or hidden.  Why it chooses to hide vs crop in some cases I can not explain, apple either made it like that or it is a bug in macOS ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è \r\n\r\nA possible workaround to this is implementing a new touch bar item which contains a [`NSScrollView`](https://developer.apple.com/reference/appkit/nsscrollview?language=objc) so that long labels can just be scrollable üëç "
  },
